Andrew Sww asked a question .

  28m 
Hi, I have travel exemption and were travelling next week, however Home Affairs website says exemption must be between 2 weeks and 2 months, ours will be a week over the two months will this be an issue?
2 Answers
Like
Answer

6 Comments

All Answers
  • Nicole Festing
    Admin
    No it won't be a problem if you have a valid unused exemption.
    The 2 days - 2 weeks guidance is about when to apply, not when you must travel.

Jason Sanderson asked a question .

  36m 
Concerning Stat Dec's, do each of us need to write and submit our own stat Dec, or can one be done that covers the whole family?
Added by admin
#statdec
1 1
2 Answers
Like
Answer

2 Comments

All Answers
  • Nicole Festing
    Admin
    As already advised, for outbound 3+ month applications - there should be one stat dec each per adult in the application.
    Some manage to get approved with only one for the family, but more commonly it is an easily fixed reason for rejection.
    •   
      Like
    •   
      Reply
    •   35m
